html~create basic template
..creating basic template
html~
============================================================
<Mode details>

html~chmod
change mode to:  html
<valid mode> changing mode to "html"
html~mode
current mode:  html
html~mode help
Modes	Description
-----	-----------
css		Cascading Style Sheets (CSS); accepts valid CSS input
html	HyperText Markup Language (HTML); acepts valid HTML code
JS		JavaScript (JS) programming language; accepts valid code
jQ		jQuery (jQ) programming library extension of JS; accepts JS command input

Flags
-----
[-g]	shows current mode
[-h]	displays all mode descriptions and related info
[-l]	lists all valid modes

Related Command
---------------
chmod [new_mode]	if valid, switches to 'new_mode'
 
 html~
============================================================
<advanced input cmmd sequence>

html~create template -hvy -s chmod css create template -hvy -s
..creating heavy template

..saving into HTML file name:  sample
..sample.html created with heavy HTML template

..<valid mode> changing mode to "css"
..creating heavy template

..saving into CSS file name:  example
..example.css created with heavy CSS template

css~get file link to sample.html
..found CSS file:  example.css
..linking "example.css" to "sample.html"
..DONE

css~
**display line number in "sample.html" where <link> links it to "example.css"**
